description: Detectives have launched a murder investigation following her death.
title: Women in her 40s who died in Lowestoft flat named
title_page: Women in her 40s who died in Lowestoft flat named - BBC News
maintext:
A woman who died in a flat has been named locally.
Suffolk Police were called to London Road South, Lowestoft, at 07:10 GMT on Saturday, after East of England Ambulance Service paramedics reported the "sudden death" of a woman in her 40s.
The woman has since been named as Kelly Anderson on social media by family.
A 49-year-old man from Lowestoft was arrested on suspicion of murder and has been bailed until the end of May.
